msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Cosmography containing a compendium of place names, seas, and mountains; information on flora and fauna; and a brief explanation of the game of chess. This text has also been attributed to the 14th-century author Zayn al-Dīn ʻUmar ibn al-Muẓaffar ibn al-Wardī.

author.persName: Ibn al-Wardī, Sirāj al-Dīn Abū Ḥafṣ ʻUmar, -1457
ابن الوردي، سراج الدين ابو حفص عمر،

respStmt.persName: Ibn al-Wardī, Zayn al-Dīn ʻUmar ibn al-Muẓaffar, -1349
ابن الوردي، زين الدين عمر بن المظفر،

supportDesc.extent: 268 leaves : 195 x 134 (146 x 85) mm bound to 195 x 160 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 15 long lines (f. 1r-79v) and 17 long lines (f. 80r-267v).

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh with a not very oblique cut pen, with chapter headings in larger muḥaqqaq script.

decoDesc.decoNote: Schematic world map in green, yellow, red, and black, across a full opening (f. 3v-4r), showing Europe, Africa and the Nile, and Asia; diagram in red and black of directions of prayer toward Mecca with the Kaʻbah in the center (f. 66r); diagram in red and black of chess game (f. 264r); some words in red, red dots marking ends of sentences.

binding.p: Bound in brown leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); blind stamped central mandorla and frame with repeating geometric pattern, gold tooling around the mandorla and gold tooled square designs on fore-edge hinge flap; scalloped edge doublures.

origin.p: The item is undated, though it was possibly produced in the mid-to-late 15th or early 16th century. The colophon has been partially pasted over.

history.provenance: Ownership inscription dated 1090/1679 (inside lower cover); later inscriptions in a maghribi hand including the name Ibn al-Maʼmūn (inside upper cover); sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, December 2009.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2013.
